title: Film Screening: Green on Thursdays
description: Activist and community resident, David Clayton will screen the award-winning documentary, Green On Thursdays, directed by Dean Bushala and Deirdre Heaslip. In addition, Mr. Clayton will share some of the many highlights of his life and work, including being a founding member of Chicago's Pink Angels--a non-profit, LGBT, community-based anti-violence squad that patrolled the streets of Chicago's Northside gay community. Green on Thursdays was nominated into the LGBT Hall of Fame. Please join us for this special, timely, and important event.

title: Never Alone: A PS4 Game
description: Never Alone is a fun and beautifully designed platform game based on Inupiat (Alaskan Native people) culture. You can play as the intrepid Inupiat girl Nuna or as her trusty artic fox companion. Two players can play both characters collaboratively as they embark upon an arctic adventure. About 40 Alaska Native community members contributed to the story and characters in Never Alone. The game will be played on a Playstation 4.

title: Ehdrigohr: Native American Role Playing Game
description: Legendary local game designer Allen Turner will walk you through his Native American themed role playing game Ehdrigohr. Successfully funded through a Kickstarter campaign, Ehdrigohr is a Fate Core based tabletop game where one plays a character struggling to survive in this recovering world. In this fantasy game of high heroics, myth and culture, powerful magic and survival horror, you become a warrior, storyteller and reality weaving Way-walker. Ehdrigohr is a game of hope.

description: Do you have a sense of style? Do you like to accessorize or make your own clothes? Join us to learn the basics of sewing, pattern making, CosPlay, deconstruction and much more and get certified to use a sewing machine!

title: Photo & Video
description: Explore the creative possibilities a pro-level camera can offer in video and photography. From there, you can explore a range of options - from music videos to narrative and experimental shorts in video, to portrait, conceptual and documentary styles in photography. Learn technical skills as well as artistic concepts and principles that will lead to the most unique and creative ways to capture people, places, topics, thoughts and emotions.

title: Art of Origami
description: Come join Jun, the Children's Librarian at the Little Village branch to create amazing animals and much more.

title: The Absolutely True Diary of A Part-Time Indian
description: In The Absolutely True Diary of A Part-time Indian, Arnold Spirit "Junior", a talented cartoonist and writer growing up on the Spokane Indian Reservation, makes a fateful decision to attend an all-white farm town high school where the only other Indian is the school mascot. He faces trouble fitting in with his white peers while he is also the target of bullies and ridicule back on the rez, adding up to a nuanced view of culture, identity, and community. Little, Brown Books For Young Readers, 2009. (Ages 12 & Up)
